{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Backend interface for cluster state storage with watcher and close", "note": "Located backend.Backend at lib/backend/backend.go:48 and backend.Watcher at lib/backend/backend.go:189 — this anchored the entire audit definition and I cited backend.go:48 in the final answer without opening the file."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "cache.Cache (file: lib/cache/cache.go)", "note": "Pinned cache.Cache at lib/cache/cache.go:532, which I cited as the cache-over-storage target. Also correctly surfaced composed_by holders inventory.InventoryCacheConfig (lib/cache/inventory/inventory_cache.go:325), cache.genericGetter (generic_operations.go:30) and genericLister (:68) — all four appeared in my final list, confirmed independently by the type checker."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "inherited_by/composed_by gave the lib/services/local service set (access.go:40, users.go:66, presence.go:53, trust.go:44, etc.) and auth.Server at lib/auth/auth.go:1308, service.TeleportProcess at lib/service/service.go:658 — every one of these reappeared in my verified 435, so the structural spine of the audit was right."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache", "note": "direct_callers_by_area gave a correct area histogram (lib/scopes/cache, lib/services, tool/tsh, lib/cache/inventory) that shaped how I grouped the final report."}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend (retained_via_interfaces)", "note": "Of ~455 rows, the integrations/access/* block (accesslist.App app.go:50, jira.App app.go:69, slack.ReviewApp review.go:60, ~20 more, all via:Client) are gRPC API-client holders that never touch backend.Backend. Rows via:UploadHandler (recordingmetadatav1 recordingmetadata.go:61), via:Authorizer (recordingmetadatav1 service.go:43), via:FS (boundkeypair.FSClientState boundkeypair.go:86), via:Semaphores, via:UsageEventsClient are not storage handles at all. I discarded these."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend vs cache.Cache retained_via_interfaces", "note": "The two lists came back ~452 and ~455 rows and near-identical despite the symbols having different method sets — a strong tell the retained list is 'reachable from', not 'retains'. That non-discrimination is what made me stop trusting it as an audit."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "note": "False negatives too: dbobjectv1.Backend (service.go:43/68), gitserverv1.Config.Backend (service.go:51), notificationsv1.Backend (service.go:42/74) were listed as backend retainers, but the type checker shows those interfaces are satisfied by lib/services/local services, not by backend.Backend — right answer for the wrong reason, and it hid that this was a distinct second tier."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend / cache.Cache", "note": "Both truncated ('retained_trimmed': true, 'hidden': 135/147) with no pagination parameter, so the candidate set was never fully retrievable."},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "cluster state storage backend read watch resources", "note": "Top hits were lib/teleterm/clusters/storage.go (Connect-client profile storage) and lib/auth/storage ProcessStorage — neither is the cluster-state layer. Keyword 'storage' beat the actual concept; I had to reword to find backend.Backend."}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend + cache.Cache retained_via_interfaces", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Verified retention. The note says 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' and it was trimmed at ~135 of 452. For an audit where a miss ships a broken service, an unverified truncated candidate list is not answerable, so I wrote a go/packages+go/types program over ./... to compute interface satisfaction exactly — that produced the 435 holders I actually reported."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache", "fallback": "read", "missing": "No way to distinguish an incidental match from a real one. My own tool hit the same trap (io.Closer matched because Backend has Close(), 24 false hits at lib/srv/ctx.go:366, lib/utils/utils.go:311 etc.) — Sense gives no method-set overlap info on a retained row that would let me filter that class."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "backend.Backend", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Ranked/typed struct fields. composed_by told me auth.Server and TeleportProcess compose Backend but not which field or at what line; I needed Server.bk at lib/auth/auth.go:1311 and TeleportProcess.backend at lib/service/service.go:671, which only the AST walk gave me."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Test vs production separation on the retained list. 'production_affected: 72 / test_affected: 14' is given for affected_symbols but retained_via_interfaces rows carry no such flag, and it mixed integrations/lib/testing/integration/accessrequestsuite.go:87 in with real holders."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "cache.Cache", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Line-accurate field positions. I spot-checked lib/auth/accesspoint/accesspoint.go:89, lib/services/local/users.go:67, lib/auth/crownjewel/crownjewelv1/service.go:85 with sed before trusting my own tool's line numbers — Sense's holder rows point at the struct decl line, not the retaining field line, and the task demanded field-level file:line."}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query_before": "cluster state storage backend read watch resources", "query_after": "Backend interface for cluster state storage with watcher and close", "hint": "First search returned lib/teleterm/clusters/storage.go and lib/auth/storage as top hits — obviously the wrong 'storage'. I rewrote around the watch/close lifecycle wording from the ticket, which surfaced backend.Watcher (backend.go:189) and backend.Backend (backend.go:48) as the top two."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "cache.Cache", "query_after": "cache.Cache with file: lib/cache/cache.go", "hint": "The sense_search result listing readonly.Cache (lib/services/readonly/cache.go:42), accessmonitoring.Cache (lib/accessmonitoring/cache.go:38) and cache.Cache alongside each other showed 'Cache' was ambiguous across packages, so I added the file disambiguator on both the graph and blast calls rather than risk resolving to the wrong Cache."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "backend.Backend", "query_after": "wrote a go/types analysis instead of further Sense calls", "hint": "'retained_note: ... Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' plus 'retained_trimmed: true' and \"completeness: partial, hidden: 135\" together told me the tool could not close this question, and the suggested next_steps ('blast a listed holder to go deeper') implied ~450 follow-up calls. That is what moved me off Sense to the type checker."}
  ],
  "q4_value": "Orientation and the correct target definition in two calls: sense_search fixed backend.Backend (lib/backend/backend.go:48) as 'the cluster-state storage layer' and sense_graph's inherited_by/composed_by handed me the whole lib/services/local service spine plus auth.Server and TeleportProcess as the aggregates — in a 5,719-file Go repo that framing would have cost me many grep rounds, and every one of those symbols survived into the verified 435. The retained_via_interfaces list was also directionally right that the answer lives behind small local interfaces named Cache/Reader/AccessPoint, which is exactly the class the ticket said was easy to miss.",
  "q5_improve": "Make retained_via_interfaces auditable instead of suggestive: (a) emit the retaining field's own file:line and field name, not the struct declaration line; (b) report the concrete satisfier set actually reachable from the constructor wiring, or at minimum a confidence flag separating 'type-checked: this interface is satisfied by the target' from 'name-similar/reachable' — that single distinction would have removed the whole integrations/access via:Client block and the io.Closer-style incidental matches; (c) let me page the trimmed remainder (offset/limit) rather than reporting 'hidden: 135' with no way to retrieve them; (d) flag test vs production per row as you already do for affected_symbols.",
  "score": 6,
  "score_rationale": "Sense's graph/search were accurate and genuinely fast for orientation — backend.Backend at backend.go:48, cache.Cache at cache.go:532, and the lib/services/local spine all came free and all held up (Q1 accurate) — but the one feature that matched this task, retained_via_interfaces, was self-declared unverified, truncated at ~135 of 452, non-discriminating between two different symbols, and carried both false positives (integrations via:Client, via:UploadHandler) and a whole missing tier (dbobjectv1.Backend), so I had to write a go/types program to produce the actual 435-holder answer (Q1 wrong, Q2); that lands it at 'interchangeable-plus' — real time saved on framing, none on the deliverable."
}

